 the stocks — and generally behave as I have always behaved. But that does not mean that I shall be happy without you.... Every small thing which will remind me of you — the look of disapproval about the furniture in the rooms where you have patted cushions and spoken to the poker, every small thing which we have descried together — will always seem to me one half of a shell, one half of a penny, with the other half kept by you. Good-bye. Go away, go away. Don't write. Marry Charlie or any